The Association of Mineworkers and Construction Union (Amcu) commemorates the people killed in the Marikana Massacre on Friday. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. MARIKANA - The Association of Mineworkers and Construction Union (Amcu) commemorates the people killed in the Marikana Massacre on Friday. The event will feature speeches from injured survivors of the incident, family members of those killed, an address by Sibanye-Stillwater Lonmin CEO Neal Froneman, and an update from lawyers representing the families involved. READ: The complicated legacy of the Marikana Massacre The event commemorates 37 of the mineworkers -- three killed on 13 August and 34 killed on 16 August. In total, 44 people were killed during the protest action.